
CLASS_01:

What, How & Why?!: 
1. SDK with version(LTS) 9/10 -Software Development Kit( ASP.NET Core Framwork,   .NET Command Line Interface (CLI))
2. IDE: Visual Studio 2012 or latest community edition-Intigrated Development Environment(Code-Run-Debug)

3. Command to install project
4. Folder Structures(MVC)

5.Create a Controller(Why should I extends main controller?):[HttpGet] vs [HttpPost]

6.Create a Form and data submit and show data in the html page with TempData 
without creating any model.

<form asp-controller="test" asp-action="indexShow" method="post">
 Name:<input type="type" name="name" />
 Email:<input type="type" name="email" />
    <input type="submit" value="Submit" />
</form>

  @if (TempData["name"] != null){ <p>Your Name is: @TempData["name"]</p>}



7. Create a model and show some validation

Data Validation: তিনটিই একসাথে ব্যবহার করো-
Client-side → ভালো UX
Server-side → Security + business rules
Database → Data integrity (final protection)

	
For Server-Side-Validation:
MODEL:
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;
[Required]

CONTROLLER: 
if (!ModelState.IsValid) { return View(model); }

VIEW:
 Name:<input type="type" asp-for="name" />




Brower-Side-Validaition:
Model exist but  [Required] না থাকলেও validation হয় কারণ সেটা browser/HTML validation, ASP.NET Core model validation নয়।






